task.summary: found bug: root directory not scanned as a "_model" directory, fixed.
Improved Indexing speed, script finds directory leaves and removes them from main index list.

Improved Indexing speed by removing directories with less than three sub_directories Found Bug: After function "Index.analyzeDirectorySkeleton" was changed to running off "self.sub_directories", the for-loop was not removed in "Index.cycle" and that cause the function to run as many times as there are elements in the "self.sub_directory" list.
renamed variable "self.sub_directories" to "self.directories" removed variable "self.finalDirectoryList" as it became depreciated
added artifact creation function in File class cleaned up baseTools.py
Added "Directory" class to baseTools , generalised functions to do with directories
added get_file_size() to Directory added get_directory_size() to Directory

added config.yml - stores base-names for directories, blacklist config added function in baseTools to find config file if moved added class "Config" - responsible for working with config.yml added function to retrieve data on base-names from config.yml called "retrieve_basename_data" cleaned up Basename class in SkeletonIndex to retrieve base-names from config.yml
added ""clean_raw_data" to class Config in FileTransfer.py - allows to retrieve specific config data from general data fixed type in config.yml in blacklist: from "enarbled" -> "enabled"

removed class Basename from SkeletonIndex moved everything from FileTransfer to baseTools moved get_branches from SkeletonIndex to baseTools cleaned up Config class added get_appropriate_size in Directory added index_photo_directory in Directory added get_specific_basename_data to Config (replacement for Basename class) created Data class in fileAnalysis which will create data on a photo directory
fixed get_appropriate_size in Directory in baseTools fixed get_specific_basename_data fixed get_basename_data added file extensions to config
